Refactor sparse operations and tree matrix multiplication
- Updated sparse matrix multiplication function to improve efficiency and clarity. - Simplified the sparse attention implementation, enhancing memory efficiency. - Introduced a new TreeMatMul class for hierarchical matrix multiplication with adaptive depth masking. - Added CUDA kernel templates for common operations, including matrix multiplication and element-wise operations. - Created unit tests for various operations, including activation functions, hybrid matrix multiplication, tree matrix multiplication, sparse operations, and efficient parallel operations. - Improved TPU kernel imports for better organization and clarity.

Implement TPU-optimized kernels for Flash Attention, GEMM, and Layer Normalization
- Added TPUFlashAttention class for efficient Flash Attention computation with O(1) memory complexity. - Introduced TPUGEMMKernel for optimized General Matrix Multiplication with support for mixed precision and tiling. - Created TPULayerNormKernel for layer normalization with options for bias, scaling, and fused operations. - Each kernel includes forward and backward pass methods, ensuring compatibility with TPU hardware. - Implemented dynamic padding and layout optimization for improved performance on TPU.
